reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Colorful Die Cast Toys
reviews.reviewText: These colorful die-cast airplanes are just the right size for small hands. Pull back friction powered, fun for all kids. There are three in this set and it will make a wonderful Holiday gift for a child who loves planes. We know just the 5 year old girl who loves to play with planes from balsa wood gliders to her super size ride on plane on the patio. She will love these and we are so happy to have found the perfect gift for her. We recommend this product.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Cute Airplane Set
reviews.reviewText: This is a charming set of biplanes. The planes have the kind of wind up motors and wheels you get in toys where you pull it back to wind it and then release. The motors are good enough that on a hard floor they’ll go forward, do a ground loop, and then continue in another direction! Surprisingly fun. The wings are plastic, the bodies are metal, and the propellers which are free spinning are plastic. There are no sharp edges and there are three planes. This is for a grandson who is airplane crazy and I’m sure will be a hit with him. Just be aware they give you the dimensions in the ad, but they also show them much larger than they really are.

reviews.reviewText: These planes are smaller than I anticipated, cute and bright colors, I like that they can be pulled back and when I let them go on the floor they zoom across it, they're supposed to be diecast,but the wings, propeller,underpart and wheels are plastic,the planes are very lightweight, still cute gifts as stocking stuffers.
